{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853863333,"sessionID":"ses_286dcffabffetpEmjLqi8ssp8o","part":{"id":"prt_d79237ccf001lUUKBkEeqQdNmU","messageID":"msg_d792372cc001bO46ScuS9kStbh","sessionID":"ses_286dcffabffetpEmjLqi8ssp8o","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2d0711289b314f188ac99420","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022: CLI publish 命令 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** L\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: <!-- TODO: 添加详细的 delta requirements，使用 Given/When/Then 格式 -->\n13: \n14: ## File changes\n15: \n16: <!-- TODO: 列出新增/修改的文件 -->\n17: \n18: | Action | File | Description |\n19: |--------|------|-------------|\n20: | TBD    |      |             |\n\n(End of file - total 20 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022: CLI publish 命令 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** L\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n<!-- TODO: 添加详细的 delta requirements，使用 Given/When/Then 格式 -->\n\n## File changes\n\n<!-- TODO: 列出新增/修改的文件 -->\n\n| Action | File | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| TBD    |      |             |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775853863324,"end":1775853863331}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853864677,"sessionID":"ses_286dcffabffetpEmjLqi8ssp8o","part":{"id":"prt_d79238226001YAEFXA7qssI8zv","messageID":"msg_d792372cc001bO46ScuS9kStbh","sessionID":"ses_286dcffabffetpEmjLqi8ssp8o","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7635bd11879b4316974f8ab4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-021: CLI build 命令 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: `build` command entry point\n13: \n14: The system SHALL provide a `build` subcommand on the Typer application that orchestrates container image creation from a previously packaged workspace.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Command signature and options\n17: - **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and the user runs `agentcube build --help`\n18: - **WHEN** the help text is displayed\n19: - **THEN** it SHALL show the following options:\n20:   - `-f, --workspace TEXT` — Path to the agent workspace directory (default: `.`)\n21:   - `-p, --proxy TEXT` — Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\n22:   - `--cloud-provider TEXT` — Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n23:   - `--output TEXT` — Output path for build artifacts\n24:   - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Default option values\n27: - **GIVEN** the user runs `agentcube build` with no options\n28: - **WHEN** the command resolves its arguments\n29: - **THEN** the values SHALL be:\n30:   - `workspace` = `\".\"`\n31:   - `proxy` = `None`\n32:   - `cloud_provider` = `None`\n33:   - `output` = `None`\n34:   - `verbose` = `False`\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Workspace path resolution\n37: - **GIVEN** the user provides a workspace path via `-f` or `--workspace`\n38: - **WHEN** the command starts execution\n39: - **THEN** the path SHALL be resolved to an absolute `Path` object before being passed to `BuildRuntime`\n40: \n41: ### Requirement: Build mode resolution\n42: \n43: The system SHALL determine the build strategy (local vs cloud) from workspace metadata, with CLI overrides taking precedence.\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Default to local build mode\n46: - **GIVEN** a workspace with `agent_metadata.yaml` containing `build_mode: local` (or no `build_mode` field)\n47: - **WHEN** the `build` command runs without `--cloud-provider`\n48: - **THEN** the system SHALL execute a local Docker build via `BuildRuntime._build_local`\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Cloud build mode via cloud provider flag\n51: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--cloud-provider huawei`\n52: - **WHEN** the command resolves the build mode\n53: - **THEN** the system SHALL execute a cloud build via `BuildRuntime._build_cloud` regardless of metadata `build_mode`\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Cloud build mode from metadata\n56: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` contains `build_mode: cloud`\n57: - **WHEN** the `build` command runs without `--cloud-provider`\n58: - **THEN** the system SHALL execute a cloud build via `BuildRuntime._build_cloud`\n59: \n60: ### Requirement: Build prerequisites validation\n61: \n62: The system SHALL validate all prerequisites before attempting a build.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Docker availability check for local builds\n65: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `local`\n66: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites` runs\n67: - **THEN** it SHALL call `DockerService.check_docker_available()` and raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` if Docker is unavailable\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Workspace packaging validation\n70: - **GIVEN** the workspace has not been packaged (no `agent_metadata.yaml` exists)\n71: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` is called\n72: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `ValueError` indicating the workspace must be packaged first\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: Metadata load success\n75: - **GIVEN** a valid `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n76: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` loads metadata\n77: - **THEN** it SHALL use `MetadataService.load_metadata` to parse the file into an `AgentMetadata` object\n78: \n79: ### Requirement: Version increment on build\n80: \n81: The system SHALL automatically increment the semantic version in metadata before building and handle rollback on failure.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Patch version increment\n84: - **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `\"1.2.3\"` (valid semver `X.Y.Z`)\n85: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._increment_version` runs\n86: - **THEN** the version SHALL become `\"1.2.4\"` (patch bumped)\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Append `.1` for non-semver versions\n89: - **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `\"1.0-beta\"` (not valid semver)\n90: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._increment_version` runs\n91: - **THEN** the version SHALL become `\"1.0-beta.1\"`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Fallback version when version is None\n94: - **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `None` or empty\n95: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._increment_version` runs\n96: - **THEN** the version SHALL become `\"0.0.1\"`\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: Version rollback on build failure\n99: - **GIVEN** the version was incremented before the build\n100: - **WHEN** `_build_local` or `_build_cloud` raises an exception\n101: - **THEN** the system SHALL revert `metadata.version` to its original value before re-raising\n102: \n103: ### Requirement: Local Docker build\n104: \n105: The system SHALL build a container image using the local Docker daemon when `build_mode` is `local`.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Successful local build\n108: - **GIVEN** Docker is available and the workspace contains a valid `Dockerfile` (generated by `pack`)\n109: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_local` runs\n110: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n111:   1. Resolve the image name from metadata (or derive from `agent_name`)\n112:   2. Call `DockerService.build_image` with the workspace `Dockerfile` path\n113:   3. Pass `build_args` containing proxy settings if `--proxy` was provided\n114:   4. Tag the image with the incremented version (default `\"latest\"` if no version)\n115:   5. Return a dict with `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Proxy configuration for local build\n118: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--proxy http://proxy.example.com:8080`\n119: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n120: - **THEN** `build_args` SHALL include `{\"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\", \"HTTPS_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\"}`\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Build with custom output path\n123: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--output /tmp/build-artifacts`\n124: - **WHEN** the local build completes\n125: - **THEN** build artifacts (if any) SHALL be saved or referenced at the specified output path\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Docker build failure\n128: - **GIVEN** the `Dockerfile` has syntax errors or build steps fail\n129: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n130: - **THEN** it SHALL raise a `docker.errors.BuildError` which propagates through `_handle_error`\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Image tag from metadata version\n133: - **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `\"1.2.4\"` after increment\n134: - **WHEN** `_build_local` tags the image\n135: - **THEN** the image SHALL be tagged as `{image_name}:1.2.4`\n136: \n137: ### Requirement: Cloud build\n138: \n139: The system SHALL trigger a remote build on the specified cloud provider when `build_mode` is `cloud`.\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Cloud build with provider\n142: - **GIVEN** `--cloud-provider huawei` is passed\n143: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_cloud` runs\n144: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n145:   1. Authenticate with the cloud provider (using configured credentials)\n146:   2. Upload the workspace contents to the cloud build service\n147:   3. Trigger the build with the specified proxy (if any)\n148:   4. Poll for build completion\n149:   5. Return a dict with cloud build result metadata\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Cloud build without provider configured\n152: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `cloud` but no `--cloud-provider` is passed and metadata lacks provider config\n153: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_cloud` runs\n154: - **THEN** it SHALL raise a `ValueError` indicating the cloud provider must be specified\n155: \n156: ### Requirement: Build metadata update\n157: \n158: The system SHALL update workspace metadata with build results upon successful completion.\n159: \n160: #### Scenario: Update build metadata on success\n161: - **GIVEN** a successful local or cloud build\n162: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata` runs\n163: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n164:   1. Update `metadata.image` with the built image information (`image_name`, `image_id`, `tag`)\n165:   2. Persist the updated metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml` via `MetadataService.save_metadata`\n166:   3. Include `build_time` in the metadata if available\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: Metadata update with custom tag\n169: - **GIVEN** the build succeeded and a specific tag is provided\n170: - **WHEN** `_update_build_metadata` runs with `tag=\"v1.2.4\"`\n171: - **THEN** the metadata `image` field SHALL include `\"tag\": \"v1.2.4\"`\n172: \n173: ### Requirement: CLI success output\n174: \n175: The system SHALL display a Rich-formatted success message after a successful build.\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Successful build output\n178: - **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build` completes without exception\n179: - **WHEN** the `build` command finishes\n180: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print:\n181:   - A success message with the agent name\n182:   - The resolved workspace path\n183:   - The built image name and tag\n184:   - Build duration (if available)\n185:   - Using Rich markup for formatting\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Verbose build output\n188: - **GIVEN** `--verbose` is passed\n189: - **WHEN** the build runs\n190: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display detailed logging including:\n191:   - Build mode resolution\n192:   - Prerequisites validation steps\n193:   - Docker build stream output (for local builds)\n194:   - Metadata update confirmation\n195: \n196: ### Requirement: Error handling\n197: \n198: The system SHALL handle build failures gracefully with appropriate error messages.\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Build error with verbose flag\n201: - **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build` raises an exception\n202: - **WHEN** `--verbose` is `True`\n203: - **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL:\n204:   1. Print `Error building agent: {e}` in red\n205:   2. Print a full traceback\n206:   3. Exit with code `1`\n207: \n208: #### Scenario: Build error without verbose flag\n209: - **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build` raises an exception\n210: - **WHEN** `--verbose` is `False`\n211: - **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL:\n212:   1. Print `Error building agent: {e}` in red\n213:   2. Exit with code `1` (no traceback)\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: Invalid workspace path\n216: - **GIVEN** the workspace path does not exist\n217: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` is called\n218: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `ValueError` with a message indicating the path is invalid\n219: \n220: ### Requirement: Progress indication\n221: \n222: The system SHALL display a Rich `Progress` spinner during the build operation.\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: Progress spinner during build\n225: - **GIVEN** the build command is running\n226: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` is executing\n227: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL show a Rich `Progress` spinner with the text `\"Building agent...\"`\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Progress completion\n230: - **GIVEN** the build completes successfully\n231: - **WHEN** the spinner stops\n232: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL replace the spinner with a success checkmark and summary\n233: \n234: ## File changes\n235: \n236: | Action | File | Description |\n237: |--------|------|-------------|\n238: | Modify | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Add `build` Typer command with options and error handling |\n239: | Modify | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Implement `build`, `_increment_version`, `_validate_build_prerequisites`, `_build_local`, `_build_cloud`, `_update_build_metadata` |\n240: | Modify | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Implement `build_image` with proxy build_args support |\n241: | Modify | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Ensure `load_metadata` and `save_metadata` support build workflow |\n242: | Modify | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Ensure `BuildRuntime` is exported |\n243: | Add | `tests/cli/test_build.py` | CLI build command tests |\n244: | Add | `tests/runtime/test_build_runtime.py` | BuildRuntime unit tests |\n245: | Add | `tests/services/test_docker_service.py` | DockerService build tests |\n\n(End of file - total 245 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-021: CLI build 命令 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: `build` command entry point\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `build` subcommand on the Typer application that orchestrates container image creation from a previously packaged workspace.\n\n#### Scenario: Command signature and options\n- **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and the user runs `agentcube build --help`\n- **WHEN** the help text is displayed\n- **THEN** it SHALL show the following options:\n  - `-f, --workspace TEXT` — Path to the agent workspace directory (default: `.`)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775853864669,"end":1775853864675}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775853864755,"sessionID":"ses_286dcffabffetpEmjLqi8ssp8o","part":{"id":"prt_d79238726001rnjicaksGYxMM7","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d792372cc001bO46ScuS9kStbh","sessionID":"ses_286dcffabffetpEmjLqi8ssp8o","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":39312,"input":39111,"output":156,"reasoning":45,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.011126487}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775853866672,"sessionID":"ses_286dcffabffetpEmjLqi8ssp8o","part":{"id":"prt_d79238eac001p7gsSctf80GHCh","messageID":"msg_d79238746001BvzGy70RrXlhid","sessionID":"ses_286dcffabffetpEmjLqi8ssp8o","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853948226,"sessionID":"ses_286dcffabffetpEmjLqi8ssp8o","part":{"id":"prt_d7923b11e001B9Scgtw2a4B8WN","messageID":"msg_d79238746001BvzGy70RrXlhid","sessionID":"ses_286dcffabffetpEmjLqi8ssp8o","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_2fc5dc81e4ac4425b22b14f8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-022: CLI publish 命令 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** L\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: `publish` command entry point\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `publish` subcommand on the Typer application that orchestrates agent deployment to either AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or standard Kubernetes.\n\n#### Scenario: Command signature and options\n- **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and the user runs `agentcube publish --help`\n- **WHEN** the help text is displayed\n- **THEN** it SHALL show the following options:\n  - `-f, --workspace TEXT` — Path to the agent workspace directory (default: `.`)\n  - `--version TEXT` — Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\n  - `--image-url TEXT` — Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\n  - `--image-username TEXT` — Username for image repository\n  - `--image-password TEXT` — Password for image repository\n  - `--description TEXT` — Agent description\n  - `--region TEXT` — Deployment region\n  - `--cloud-provider TEXT` — Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n  - `--provider TEXT` — Target provider: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment/Service) (default: `agentcube`)\n  - `--node-port INTEGER` — Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\n  - `--replicas INTEGER` — Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\n  - `--namespace TEXT` — The namespace for the deployment\n  - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n\n#### Scenario: Default option values\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `agentcube publish` with no options\n- **WHEN** the command resolves its arguments\n- **THEN** the values SHALL be:\n  - `workspace` = `\".\"`\n  - `version` = `None`\n  - `image_url` = `None`\n  - `image_username` = `None`\n  - `image_password` = `None`\n  - `description` = `None`\n  - `region` = `None`\n  - `cloud_provider` = `None`\n  - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`\n  - `node_port` = `None`\n  - `replicas` = `None`\n  - `namespace` = `None`\n  - `verbose` = `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Workspace path resolution\n- **GIVEN** the user provides a workspace path via `-f` or `--workspace`\n- **WHEN** the command starts execution\n- **THEN** the path SHALL be resolved to an absolute `Path` object before being passed to `PublishRuntime`\n\n### Requirement: Provider validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate the `--provider` option and route to the correct publish flow.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid provider values\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--provider agentcube` or `--provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the command validates the provider\n- **THEN** the system SHALL accept the value and instantiate `PublishRuntime` with the corresponding `provider` argument\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid provider value\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--provider invalid-provider`\n- **WHEN** the command validates the provider\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `ValueError` indicating the provider must be `agentcube` or `k8s`\n\n### Requirement: Image preparation for publishing\n\nThe system SHALL prepare the container image for deployment by either pushing a local image to a registry or using an explicit image URL from metadata.\n\n#### Scenario: Image preparation dispatch by build mode\n- **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing` is called\n- **WHEN** `metadata.build_mode` is `local`\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `_prepare_local_image` and return the resulting image reference\n- **WHEN** `metadata.build_mode` is `cloud`\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `_prepare_cloud_image` and return the resulting image reference\n\n#### Scenario: Local image preparation with CLI credentials\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `local` and the user passes `--image-url`, `--image-username`, and `--image-password`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Call `DockerService._docker_login_sdk` with the provided credentials\n  2. Call `DockerService._tag_image_sdk` to tag the local image for the target registry\n  3. Call `DockerService.push_image` to push the image to the registry\n  4. Return the full image reference (registry URL + image name + tag)\n\n#### Scenario: Local image preparation without credentials\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `local` and no `--image-username`/`--image-password` is provided\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL attempt to push using credentials from metadata (`registry_username`, `registry_password`) if present, or skip login if the registry allows anonymous push\n\n#### Scenario: Local image preparation requires image URL\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `local` and no `--image-url` is provided\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL check metadata for `image` field; if absent, raise `ValueError` indicating image URL is required for local build mode\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud image preparation\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `cloud`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_cloud_image` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Resolve the image reference from metadata `image` field or `--image-url`\n  2. Return the image reference without performing Docker operations\n\n### Requirement: AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR) publish flow\n\nThe system SHALL deploy an AgentRuntime custom resource to Kubernetes when `provider` is `agentcube`.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube prerequisites — required URLs\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n- **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube prerequisites — readiness probe fields\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n- **WHEN** metadata lacks `readiness_probe_path` or `readiness_probe_port`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating readiness probe configuration is required\n\n#### Scenario: Successful AgentRuntime CR deployment\n- **GIVEN** all prerequisites are met and `provider` is `agentcube`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Prepare the image reference via `_prepare_image_for_publishing`\n  2. Call `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` with `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `env_vars`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`\n  3. Update metadata with deployment info via `_update_publish_metadata`\n  4. Return a dict with `status`, `agent_name`, `namespace`, `agent_id`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR deployment with namespace override\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--namespace production`\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `production` as the namespace instead of the default `default`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR deployment with version override\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--version v2.0.0`\n- **WHEN** `_publish_cr_to_k8s` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL update `metadata.version` to `v2.0.0` before deployment\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR deployment with description override\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--description \"My updated agent\"`\n- **WHEN** `_publish_cr_to_k8s` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL update `metadata.description` before deployment\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR deployment with region\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--region cn-north-4`\n- **WHEN** `_publish_cr_to_k8s` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL update `metadata.region` before deployment\n\n### Requirement: Standard Kubernetes provider publish flow\n\nThe system SHALL deploy a standard Kubernetes Deployment and NodePort Service when `provider` is `k8s`.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful K8s deployment\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes client initializes\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Prepare the image reference via `_prepare_image_for_publishing`\n  2. Call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` with `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `replicas`, `node_port`, `env_vars`\n  3. Call `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready` with `timeout=120`\n  4. Update metadata with deployment info via `_update_publish_metadata`\n  5. Return a dict with `status`, `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `node_port`, `service_url`\n\n#### Scenario: K8s deployment with replicas override\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--replicas 3`\n- **WHEN** `_publish_k8s` calls `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`\n- **THEN** it SHALL pass `replicas=3` instead of the default `1`\n\n#### Scenario: K8s deployment with NodePort override\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--node-port 30080`\n- **WHEN** `_publish_k8s` calls `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`\n- **THEN** it SHALL pass `node_port=30080` and the resulting `service_url` SHALL be `http://localhost:30080`\n\n#### Scenario: K8s deployment readiness timeout\n- **GIVEN** the deployment does not become ready within 120 seconds\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds the timeout\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `TimeoutError` and the system SHALL record the error in metadata before raising `RuntimeError`\n\n#### Scenario: K8s deployment with namespace override\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--namespace staging`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `staging` as the namespace for all resource creation\n\n### Requirement: Publish metadata update\n\nThe system SHALL update workspace metadata with publish results upon successful deployment.\n\n#### Scenario: Update publish metadata on success\n- **GIVEN** a successful publish (either provider)\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Update `metadata.agent_id` with the assigned agent ID\n  2. Update `metadata.agent_endpoint` with the service URL\n  3. Update `metadata.k8s_deployment` with provider-specific deployment info\n  4. Persist the updated metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml` via `MetadataService.save_metadata`\n\n#### Scenario: K8s deployment metadata structure\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and publish succeeds\n- **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** `metadata.k8s_deployment` SHALL include:\n  - `type`: `\"Deployment\"`\n  - `deployment_name`: the deployment name\n  - `service_name`: the service name\n  - `namespace`: the namespace\n  - `node_port`: the assigned NodePort\n  - `service_url`: the service URL\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR metadata structure\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and publish succeeds\n- **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** `metadata.k8s_deployment` SHALL include:\n  - `type`: `\"AgentRuntime\"`\n  - `agent_name`: the agent name\n  - `namespace`: the namespace\n  - `agent_id`: the assigned agent ID\n\n### Requirement: CLI success output\n\nThe system SHALL display a Rich-formatted success message after a successful publish.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful publish output — AgentCube provider\n- **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` completes without exception with `provider=agentcube`\n- **WHEN** the `publish` command finishes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print:\n  - A success message with the agent name\n  - The resolved workspace path\n  - The agent ID\n  - The agent endpoint URL\n  - Using Rich markup for formatting\n\n#### Scenario: Successful publish output — K8s provider\n- **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` completes without exception with `provider=k8s`\n- **WHEN** the `publish` command finishes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print:\n  - A success message with the agent name\n  - The resolved workspace path\n  - The deployment name and service name\n  - The service URL (e.g., `http://localhost:{node_port}`)\n  - Using Rich markup for formatting\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose publish output\n- **GIVEN** `--verbose` is passed\n- **WHEN** the publish runs\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display detailed logging including:\n  - Provider selection\n  - Image preparation steps\n  - Deployment progress\n  - Metadata update confirmation\n\n### Requirement: Error handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle publish failures gracefully with appropriate error messages.\n\n#### Scenario: Publish error with verbose flag\n- **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` is `True`\n- **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL:\n  1. Print `Error publishing agent: {e}` in red\n  2. Print a full traceback\n  3. Exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Publish error without verbose flag\n- **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` is `False`\n- **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL:\n  1. Print `Error publishing agent: {e}` in red\n  2. Exit with code `1` (no traceback)\n\n#### Scenario: Missing workspace\n- **GIVEN** the workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `ValueError` with a message indicating the workspace directory does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: Missing metadata file\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does not exist in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` attempts to load metadata\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `ValueError` indicating the workspace must be packaged first\n\n### Requirement: Progress indication\n\nThe system SHALL display a Rich `Progress` spinner during the publish operation.\n\n#### Scenario: Progress spinner during publish\n- **GIVEN** the publish command is running\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` is executing\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL show a Rich `Progress` spinner with the text `\"Publishing agent...\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Progress completion\n- **GIVEN** the publish completes successfully\n- **WHEN** the spinner stops\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL replace the spinner with a success checkmark and summary\n\n### Requirement: NodePort validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate the `--node-port` value when provided for K8s deployments.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid NodePort range\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--node-port 30080`\n- **WHEN** the command validates the node port\n- **THEN** the system SHALL accept the value (within 30000-32767 range)\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid NodePort — below range\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--node-port 29999`\n- **WHEN** the command validates the node port\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `ValueError` indicating NodePort must be between 30000 and 32767\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid NodePort — above range\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--node-port 32768`\n- **WHEN** the command validates the node port\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `ValueError` indicating NodePort must be between 30000 and 32767\n\n## File changes\n\n| Action | File | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| Modify | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Add `publish` Typer command with options, provider routing, and error handling |\n| Modify | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Implement `publish`, `_publish_cr_to_k8s`, `_publish_k8s`, `_prepare_image_for_publishing`, `_prepare_local_image`, `_prepare_cloud_image`, `_update_publish_metadata` |\n| Modify | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Ensure `push_image`, `_docker_login_sdk`, `_tag_image_sdk` support publish workflow |\n| Modify | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | Ensure `deploy_agent_runtime` supports all publish parameters |\n| Modify | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | Ensure `deploy_agent` and `wait_for_deployment_ready` support publish workflow |\n| Modify | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Ensure metadata save supports publish workflow |\n| Add | `tests/cli/test_publish.py` | CLI publish command tests |\n| Add | `tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py` | PublishRuntime unit tests |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775853948207,"end":1775853948223}}}}
